{"success":true,"rfi_draft":"**CONFIDENTIAL / URGENT**\n\n**Date:** October 24, 2023\n\n**To,**\nThe Audit Committee & Board of Directors,\nReliance Industries Limited (RELIANCE.NS),\nMaker Chambers IV, Nariman Point,\nMumbai - 400 021, Maharashtra, India.\n\n**Subject: Request for Information (RFI) – Notice of Specific Anomalies Detected in Related Party Transactions (RPT) via Project IRIS**\n\n**Dear Members of the Board and the Audit Committee,**\n\nThis communication serves as a formal Request for Information regarding certain financial disclosures and transaction patterns of Reliance Industries Limited (“the Company”). \n\nA comprehensive forensic audit and data-integrity review, conducted under the auspices of **Project IRIS**—an advanced AI-driven forensic surveillance initiative—has flagged specific anomalies concerning the Company’s Related Party Transactions (RPT). These findings necessitate a granular review to ensure adherence to the prevailing corporate governance framework.\n\n**Regulatory Framework:**\nYour attention is directed to the statutory requirements under:\n1.  **Regulation 23 of the SEBI (Listing Obligations and Disclosure Requirements) Regulations, 2015**, which mandates strict approval processes and disclosure norms for RPTs.\n2.  **Section 188 of the Companies Act, 2013**, regarding the consent and pricing mechanisms for transactions with related parties.\n3.  **Ind AS 24**, pertaining to the transparency of related party disclosures in financial statements.\n\n**Observations & Findings:**\nPreliminary forensic analytics from Project IRIS have identified variances that suggest potential deviations from the \"Ordinary Course of Business\" and \"Arm’s Length\" standards required by law. While a general forensic review has been initiated, the initial data clusters indicate inconsistencies between declared related party interests and the underlying transactional flow.\n\n**Information Requested:**\nIn light of the above, the Company is hereby requested to provide the following documentation and clarifications:\n1.  A detailed ledger of all transactions exceeding the materiality threshold defined under Regulation 23(1) of SEBI LODR for the last three fiscal quarters.\n2.  The specific \"Arm’s Length\" valuation reports and internal audit justifications used to approve these transactions.\n3.  Minutes of the Audit Committee meetings where the aforementioned transactions were reviewed and granted prior approval.\n4.  Clarification on any Omnibus approvals granted and the subsequent utilization of such approvals against actual transaction values.\n\n**Timeline for Compliance:**\nGiven the gravity of potential regulatory non-compliance and its impact on shareholder interest, you are requested to submit a detailed response along with the supporting documentation within **fifteen (15) business days** from the receipt of this letter.\n\nPlease be advised that this inquiry is objective and intended to ensure the integrity of the capital markets. Failure to provide satisfactory clarification within the stipulated timeframe may result in further escalation to the relevant regulatory authorities for a formal investigation.\n\nWe look forward to your prompt cooperation in this matter.\n\n**Sincerely,**\n\n*(Signature)*\n\n**Compliance Officer / Lead Investigator**\nProject IRIS – Forensic Division\n[Authorized Legal/Compliance Entity]","target_committee":"Audit Committee","law_references":["SEBI LODR Reg 23","Companies Act Section 188"],"is_fallback":false}